The paper proposes a new deep learning architecture for representation learning in domains without a known structure between features. This is a common problem in machine learning, and the proposed method is likely to be of interest to researchers in several sub-fields of computer science. The paper focuses on classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The experiments involve image datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
